<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="111" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Shrub</emphasis>
1.0-1.5 m tall; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">leaves</emphasis>
coriaceous, blades 1.0-3.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 cm, elliptic to slightly ovate, yellowish-tomentose below; heads sessile, solitary or in clusters of 2-3 at apex of branches, few clusters per plant; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">involucre</emphasis>
campanulate, 15-20 mm tall 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
25
<normalizedToken originalValue="–35(–">-35(-</normalizedToken>
40) mm wide, bracts in 5-6 series, densely puberulous abaxially; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">flowers</emphasis>
200-230 per head; corollas light yellow, 13-22 mm long; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">anther</emphasis>
base caudate, tails 2.0-2.5 mm long, entire; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">pappus</emphasis>
ca. 1 cm long, bristles biseriate, broadening slightly at the apex.
</paragraph>
